    <p>A security guard in California is claiming that he was fired from his job because he was prescribed tinted glasses by his physician. The plaintiff is seeking compensation for <a href="http://www.nosratilaw.com/Discrimination/Disability.shtml" >disability discrimination</a> from his former employers, Securitas Services and Kaiser Permanente International. The man was dismissed from his position because of his disability in February.</p> <p>Official reports show that the man was hired in December 2010 as a security guard at the hospital's San Rafael facility. He had been diagnosed with photosensitivity, so he was required to wear tinted lenses in his glasses both inside and outside. Even though the man says he submitted appropriate documentation to his supervisor at the security company, his bosses still discriminated against him.</p>
    <p>The man said that he was told several times to take off his tinted glasses. Further, he was transferred to the "graveyard" shift, being forced to work the midnight to 8 a.m. shift because hospital workers found his glasses unnerving. The man was mocked by his coworkers, which caused him serious emotional distress, ultimately manifesting in migraines and crippling anxiety.</p> <p>Supervisors at both Securitas and Kaiser told the man that he was only allowed to work the nighttime shift because of his tinted glasses. Further, even though the man had specialized training that allowed him to work in the emergency department at a higher rate of pay, he was demoted to a regular security position because of the glasses.</p> <p>Something as simple as prescribed tinted glasses seems unobtrusive -- but this man suffered serious professional issues because of his disability. The American Disabilities Act protects such workers from unfair termination and unequal treatment. No California workers should have to tolerate this type of disability discrimination at their job. Financial relief may be available through the civil courts for victims of such violations.</p> <p> <b>Source:&nbsp;</b> Courthouse News Service, "<a href="http://www.courthousenews.com/2014/06/05/68463.htm" target="_blank">Kaiser Demoted Guard for Disability, He Says</a>" Barbara Wallace, Jun. 05, 2014 </p>
